AB  - This paper suggests a modification of the method of scoring in the general multivariate qualitative response model to attain simpler computation when there are many observations per cell. The paper shows that the proposed estimator is asymptotically efficient even in the cases when the generalized Berkson's estimator (see Amemiya, Journal of the American Statistical Association, June 1976) is not.
