T1  - Forecasting aggregates of independent Arima processes
AU  - Rose, David E.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 5
IS  - 3
SP  - 323
EP  - 345
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/05/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(77)90043-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407677900434
AB  - In this paper I derive the properties of linear aggregates of independent ARIMA processes, including those with seasonality. I show that such aggregates are ARIMA processes, but that multiplicative seasonal structure on the moving average side will generally break down in the aggregation. The forecasting efficiency of a direct model of an aggregate is contrasted with that of an optimal predictor which uses the structural information. The former is shown to suffer from a kind of aggregation bias, a bias which can be expressed as a mean zero stochastic process.
